## Generators & Iterators — Pause karne wale Functions ⏸️

Generator functions ek special type ke functions hain jo pause aur resume ho sakte hain — bahut useful for lazy evaluation aur infinite sequences!

### Basic Generator:
```javascript
// function* se generator banate hain
function* simpleGenerator() {
  console.log('Step 1');
  yield 1; // Pause here, 1 return karo

  console.log('Step 2');
  yield 2; // Pause again

  console.log('Step 3');
  yield 3;

  console.log('Done!');
  return 'final'; // Generator khatam
}

const gen = simpleGenerator();

console.log(gen.next()); // Step 1, {value: 1, done: false}
console.log(gen.next()); // Step 2, {value: 2, done: false}
console.log(gen.next()); // Step 3, {value: 3, done: false}
console.log(gen.next()); // Done!, {value: 'final', done: true}
console.log(gen.next()); // {value: undefined, done: true}
```

### Generators with for...of:
```javascript
function* countdown(from) {
  while (from > 0) {
    yield from--;
  }
  yield '🚀 LAUNCH!';
}

for (const value of countdown(5)) {
  console.log(value); // 5, 4, 3, 2, 1, 🚀 LAUNCH!
}

// Spread bhi kaam karta hai
